'''Couple costume''' and '''Couple look''' are [[Chinglish]] and [[Konglish]] terms, respectively, for the practice of a [[Intimate relationship|couple]] wearing the same [[hat]], [[T-shirt]], or other [[clothing]] [[Dating (activity)|in public]] to [[Impression management|signal]] their relationship. It is mainly found in [[Culture of South Korea|South Korea]] and [[Culture of Taiwan|Taiwan]], [[Culture of Vietnam|Vietnam]] and is becoming more common in [[Culture of the People's Republic of China|mainland China]] during its [[Economic reform in the People's Republic of China|reform and opening]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}}
Young Asian couples announce their relationship status by sporting the same clothes when they go out together.{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}} Today, this is a fashion trend among young couples.{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}} Couples usually wear matching T-shirts, shirts, hoodies, sweaters, and jackets or coats. These clothes are often printed with funny graphics or slogans, so that they are suitable for younger people.{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}}
==In other languages== *[[Vietnamese language]]: Áo đôi, Áo cặp (couple T-shirt),<ref name="CANIFA"> {{cite web | url= http://canifa.com/cach-mac-dep-ao-thun-cap | title= Áo thun cặp cho tình yêu thăng hoa | publisher= CANIFA }} </ref> *[[Japanese language]]: カップルTシャツ (couple T-shirt) *[[Korean language|Korean]]: 커플룩
